    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-creamy-carrot-orzo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then slice</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced carrot</strong> to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-creamy-carrot-orzo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped leek </strong>and cook for 3 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-creamy-carrot-orzo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the leek is cooking, add your <strong>orzo</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>orzo</strong> for 6-8 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>orzo</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-creamy-carrot-orzo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once tender, add the <strong>cooked carrot</strong> to the pan with your <strong>'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Keep the heat medium to avoid the 'Nduja from smoking!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-creamy-carrot-orzo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>to the pan with your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> Chinese rice wine </strong>and<strong> half </strong>your<strong> balsamic vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and cook for 1 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-creamy-carrot-orzo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the <strong>drained orzo </strong>with<strong> half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save some for a garnish!)</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>'Nduja & creamy carrot orzo</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-creamy-carrot-orzo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>'Nduja & creamy carrot orzo </strong>and top with the <strong>salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the<strong> remaining balsamic vinegar </strong>and a little<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
